Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.72,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As long as modern-day crimes involve people,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.72,0:00:06.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}there are no unsolvable mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.59,0:00:08.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's case is a train trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.36,0:00:10.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Schedules are the basis of judgment!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:12.26,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.26,0:00:14.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:16.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.93,0:01:45.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mountain Hot Spring Town\NYu-no-Yama
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.02,0:01:48.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yu-no-Yama Station
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.06,0:01:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where're we going? Aren't we getting on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.43,0:01:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this is the Hana-no-Machi Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:02:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're riding the one up there,\Nthe Yu-no-Yama Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter which one we take—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.11,0:02:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,both lines connect to a Tokyo-bound line
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.21,0:02:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at Hana-no-Machi Station anyways...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll miss the train if we don't hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.81,0:02:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My head's pounding from this hangover...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.85,0:02:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't shout so loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh. I don't feel up to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The food, the inn, and the hot spring were all great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.28,0:02:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.28,0:02:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.55,0:02:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of your clients invited you on this trip
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.29,0:02:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as a reward for solving their case!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.92,0:02:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.39,0:02:58.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Though I'm the one who solved the case, not him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:03:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna sleep for an hour until we get to Hana-no-Machi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your problem, Sato?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.85,0:03:10.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Dr. Taizo Sato
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.14,0:03:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?\NYou don't need to get so mad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.31,0:03:15.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Dr. Takashi Date
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You disgust me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't bear to sit with you any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.65,0:03:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to a different car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.52,0:03:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Date!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't they—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they stayed at the same inn as us last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.62,0:03:32.71,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kan'etsu Medical Association
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:39.33,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.04,0:03:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that group of doctors...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.71,0:03:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.84,0:03:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're from last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.68,0:03:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's just upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.72,0:03:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are the other doctors?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.48,0:03:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We all left separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:03:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some took the Hana-no-Machi Line
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:04:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while others took the Yu-no-Yama Line like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.16,0:04:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both lines end at Hana-no-Machi Station anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.73,0:04:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then. Nighty-night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:20.70,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mizu-no-Kawa! Mizu-no-Kawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.85,0:04:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mizu-no-Kawa Station?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.52,0:04:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it says we can transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.15,0:04:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should transfer to the Hana-no-Machi Line here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bzzt! Too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hana-no-Machi train arrived here at exactly 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.23,0:04:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was five minutes ago. It's long gone by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.21,0:04:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to disturb you. Tickets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.92,0:05:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.08,0:05:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.88,0:05:06.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mizu-no-Kawa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.35,0:05:14.43,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hana-no-Machi Station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:18.40,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you for using the Yu-no-Yama Line today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.40,0:05:21.40,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is our last stop, Hana-no-Machi Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:25.28,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please look around once more to avoid forgetting anything onboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:26.74,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Passengers transferring to the Tokyo-bound train
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:28.58,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}will need to switch to Platform 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.58,0:05:31.64,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The next train will leave at 11:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.75,0:05:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thirty-five minutes of waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I calmed down after looking at the scenery from the very last car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:49.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you might!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.73,0:05:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry 'bout that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds like they made up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:05:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.07,0:05:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.01,0:05:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:08.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sure has a lot of change...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it was nice to meet you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likewise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.23,0:06:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mister! Your button's about to come off!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:28.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He wiped it! How odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.31,0:06:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was the body found?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside the Hana-no-Machi train that arrived 5 minutes ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim appears to be a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it's a doctor from our group?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone did leave by themselves—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,one of them could have been on the Hana-no-Machi Line!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.39,0:06:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.17,0:06:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.93,0:06:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! What about your hangover?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:57.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't stay silent after hearing there's a dead body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.27,0:07:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Kogoro Mouri's excitement has been piqued!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Utsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was in your medical association?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.99,0:07:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Utsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. He was with us last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.69,0:07:27.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's with that look?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:33.53,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Chief Railway Officer\NYosuke Kobayashi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Chief Railway Officer Yosuke Kobayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an honor to meet you, Detective Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.74,0:07:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your cooperation is greatly appreciated!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.84,0:07:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem. I'm glad to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.92,0:07:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what was the cause of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We won't know for sure until the autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but my guess is cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.39,0:07:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, I'm of no use here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.46,0:08:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, isn't that a syringe mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You keep quiet! Wait, a syringe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the vein on his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.57,0:08:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a needle mark with blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mark from a hypodermic needle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.04,0:08:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.14,0:08:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When intravenously given high doses of potassium chloride,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,people can die with symptoms just like cardiac arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.05,0:08:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hospitals have potassium chloride and syringes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow. You sure know a lot, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really like science stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.60,0:08:36.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.17,0:08:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't see any syringes anywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.01,0:08:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was neither an accident nor a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.11,0:08:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a homicide! A murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.61,0:08:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're in the way! Go outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:08:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.01,0:08:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, then. The question is motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a simple robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.09,0:08:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's not a single yen left in his wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why are his fingers broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.36,0:09:03.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer was macho!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.63,0:09:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer held him down so hard that it broke his fingers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,prevented him from fighting back, and then committed the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.37,0:09:12.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Would they really go through the trouble of giving him a shot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.37,0:09:13.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}just for that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.44,0:09:17.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Hana-no-Machi line runs parallel to the Yu-no-Yama line,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:18.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which we took.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.71,0:09:21.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Yu-no-Yama and Mizu-no-Kawa stations
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:23.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}are the only places they meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.85,0:09:25.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The train this happened on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.48,0:09:29.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}stopped at Mizu-no-Kawa Station at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.65,0:09:31.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The question is the time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the victim bought the canned coffee at around 10:50?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.99,0:09:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had almost arrived at Hana-no-Machi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he was my last customer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.07,0:09:45.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have any 1000-yen bills to give him change with,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.34,0:09:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I gave him his change in coins, which is why I remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.24,0:09:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he sitting by himself at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.58,0:09:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.35,0:09:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And immediately afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:10:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a mustached-man in a dark blue jacket and sunglasses sat next to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.25,0:10:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you got up and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.69,0:10:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:08.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A dark blue jacket?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the crime took place between 10:50 and 10:52 or 10:53.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.77,0:10:19.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That Dr. Date's jacket is reversible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:21.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The other side is dark blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.11,0:10:26.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe his button was about to come off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.04,0:10:28.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}because the victim had grabbed it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:32.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He broke his fingers trying to remove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:34.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's why he—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.12,0:10:35.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:38.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He wiped the front of the button
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:40.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to remove the victim's fingerprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:43.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the victim died from an injection of potassium chloride,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:46.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which would be difficult for anyone but a doctor to get!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.76,0:10:49.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Plus his reaction when he heard the old man's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:53.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dr. Date's probably the one responsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:58.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But how could he have killed someone on a different train?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.51,0:11:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, aren't you going to do your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.48,0:11:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've got a search out for the robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My job here is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.12,0:11:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was this really a robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.56,0:11:16.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That witness lady seems a lot richer than the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she was sitting nearby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the killer go after the man instead of the woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a good question...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.38,0:11:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, why do you suppose that guy's sweating so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.25,0:11:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dr. Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't happen to know something, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.12,0:11:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? No, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mind. Tell him, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.89,0:11:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell him that I had a big argument with Utsumi at the inn yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An argument? With the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.77,0:12:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was a big one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What caused it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.01,0:12:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unfounded accusation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I was receiving kickbacks from a pharmaceutical company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.18,0:12:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I'm completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, man. You don't seriously think I killed him, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.39,0:12:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.16,0:12:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's clear that you and the victim were on different trains
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from what Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others have said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:31.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, Dr. Date does have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, why did you take the Yu-no-Yama Line
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.11,0:12:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,instead of the Hana-no-Machi Line?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could have ridden either one,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.68,0:12:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but Dr. Date bought me the ticket, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what was that argument earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.72,0:12:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried to pay him back for my ticket,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he refused to accept my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He suddenly got angry when I insisted he take it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know what to think when he blew up like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:00.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So Dr. Date suggested taking the Yu-no-Yama Line
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:06.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and then faked an argument to move to the rear car...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.60,0:13:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}. Can I see the train schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The train schedule? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.43,0:13:14.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:20.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If he had transferred to the Hana-no-Machi Line...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:23.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...Mizu-no-Kawa Station would be the only place to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.92,0:13:27.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the Hana-no-Machi train the victim was on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.76,0:13:31.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}arrived at Mizu-no-Kawa Station at 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.10,0:13:36.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Our Yu-no-Yama train arrived five minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:39.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Hana-no-Machi train was long gone by then!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.67,0:13:41.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe he couldn't have done it after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.87,0:13:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second! Didn't it say—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.71,0:13:46.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Yu-no-Yama Line is Line 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.61,0:13:49.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Hana-no-Machi Line is Line 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.05,0:13:54.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An overpass connects Platforms 3 and 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.55,0:13:56.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The stairs are right next to the rear car,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:14:00.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}which Dr. Date had all to himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.89,0:14:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. Sounds like I'll be held up a little bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.06,0:14:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you close the office up for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:11.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.67,0:14:13.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A cell phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.07,0:14:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no! I left Sonoko's present on the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:20.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:23.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I understand the trick Dr. Date used to switch trains!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.21,0:14:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you forgot something, then ask Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.21,0:14:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It's the killer I want you to find!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Is it my hangover?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.13,0:14:55.10,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is Kogoro Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:59.23,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Would those involved please assemble in the staff room?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.87,0:15:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've identified the real person responsible for this incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dr. Date and Dr. Sato. Please come as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.94,0:15:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real person responsible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're busy, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.18,0:15:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this all about, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, the truth will become clear in only 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.53,0:15:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying you'll point out the killer and have him arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.50,0:15:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in those 15 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.03,0:15:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, I am, Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.27,0:15:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, you're going to try to arrest me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.80,0:15:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The real person responsible for this incident
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.04,0:15:42.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is you, Dr. Date!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.54,0:15:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.05,0:15:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was on the same Yu-no-Yama train as us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can only confirm that for the first 5 minutes after the train departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't see him again until we arrived at Hana-no-Machi Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.49,0:16:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.33,0:16:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he transfer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. At Mizu-no-Kawa Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At Mizu-no-Kawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that impossible, time-wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.90,0:16:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Yu-no-Yama train arrived on Platform 1 of Mizu-no-Kawa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.28,0:16:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at 10:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.85,0:16:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long after the Hana-no-Machi train on Platform 6 had left!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.35,0:16:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I have possibly transferred trains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.72,0:16:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A single phone call would make it possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.79,0:16:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.39,0:16:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you call from a cell phone one train stop ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ask them to hold the Hana-no-Machi train
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.70,0:16:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you left something on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.34,0:16:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.11,0:16:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before you arrived at Mizu-no-Kawa Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you turned your reversible jacket inside-out
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.88,0:16:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and disguised yourself with a fake mustache and other props.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:16:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you arrived at the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:16:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you ran up the overpass
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.72,0:17:03.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and headed for Line 6 as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.29,0:17:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you started an argument with Dr. Sato
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.99,0:17:09.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and moved to the last car immediately after the train departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.93,0:17:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had the train employees search for a missing item
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.33,0:17:14.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to delay the Hana-no-Machi train's departure,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.50,0:17:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,allowing you to get on in the nick of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had probably instructed the victim to sit there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,before you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.58,0:17:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.95,0:17:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s right; there was both a phone call and a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man was distressed because he had forgotten a contract
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.65,0:17:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,more important than his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.85,0:17:37.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it never turned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.79,0:17:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow. But how exactly is that proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the call recorded and voice-matched with my voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.63,0:17:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.97,0:17:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the Yu-no-Yama train the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.14,0:17:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then please show us your ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ticket inspection took place on the Yu-no-Yama train at around 10:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:18:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you didn't transfer, then it should have a stamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.88,0:18:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we see your ticket, Date{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.32,0:18:10.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You lost it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.32,0:18:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to do a body search?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, there's no proof I was on the train the entire time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.30,0:18:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but there's no proof I transferred, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Innocent until proven guilty."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.94,0:18:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.17,0:18:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I can't waste any more time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.24,0:18:29.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.74,0:18:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which platform for the train to Tokyo, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.08,0:18:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there still something left?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.62,0:18:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You certainly had a lot of change in your wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.13,0:18:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.53,0:18:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's entirely possible that the killer took the victim's money
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.17,0:19:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from his wallet—including all of his change—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.64,0:19:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like a robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your point?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.25,0:19:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but Utsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was with me last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.26,0:19:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We both chipped in to buy cigarettes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it wouldn't be that odd to find his fingerprints
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.36,0:19:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the money inside my wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.84,0:19:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not referring to the victim's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.51,0:19:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? Whose fingerprints would there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.98,0:19:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.78,0:19:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right before he was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.52,0:19:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the victim bought canned coffee from the onboard vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.69,0:19:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was the last customer, and he pulled out a 10,000-yen bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the vendor remembers him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.13,0:20:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That train vendor's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.07,0:20:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dr. Date.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.94,0:20:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fingerprints of the vendor on the Hana-no-Machi train,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.61,0:20:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which you supposedly weren't on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.15,0:20:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they happen to be on any of the coins in your wallet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the rumor really was true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.04,0:20:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was receiving kickbacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.78,0:20:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he caught me and tried to blackmail me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.15,0:20:52.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He demanded money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.05,0:20:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said if I didn't pay up, it would become more than a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.85,0:20:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He threatened to send incriminating photographs
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.69,0:20:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to my medical association and the hospital I work at!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.56,0:21:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I decided to agree to a deal to get the film
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.13,0:21:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and kill him on the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it hard to believe he would hand over all the negatives!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.47,0:21:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someday the rumor would become the target of investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:19.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So instead, you planned to use an alibi trick involving trains
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.85,0:21:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to avoid suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:25.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the perfect plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.15,0:21:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like all of my big operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the most skilled physicians are human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunate as it may be, even they make bad diagnoses!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People are imperfect—no crime they commit will ever be flawless!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.33,0:23:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a nice nap...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.86,0:23:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hana-no-Machi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are we still here, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.97,0:23:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we're already here, let's stay another night at a hot spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.67,0:23:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hana-no-Machi Hot Spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.74,0:23:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.84,0:23:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sounds great! Let's do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.74,0:23:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.75,0:23:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But another night does sound like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.92,0:23:56.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.95,0:23:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not much, but there's a fresh scratch mark here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.19,0:24:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from something thin!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.76,0:24:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.03,0:24:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No question about it! This was a murder, not an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.94,0:24:14.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.95,0:24:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Security Camera
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.20,0:24:22.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, some very special guests!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.00,0:24:24.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hideyuki Nakayama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kuniko Asagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
